The remains of Hajia Binta, wife of former minister of defence, retired Gen Aliyu Mohammed Gusau, have been laid to rest on Tuesday, in Kaduna. Hajiya Binta died at a London Hospital. No less than six governors and other important dignitaries were present at the burial. Prayers were said for the repose of her soul at the Yahaya Road Mosque, Kaduna, while her remains were interred at the Ungwan Sarki cemetery at about 1:30 pm. Dignitaries who were at General Gusauâ€™s residence to pay their last respect are the Kaduna State governor, Malam Nasir El-rufai, Kano State governor, Umar Ganduje, and that of Sokoto, Aminu Tambuwal, Nasarawa, Tanko Al-Makura, as well as Gombe, Ibrahim Dankwambo including Adamawa, Mohammed Umar Jibrilla. Governor of Adamawa State, Jibrilla, described the late Hajia Binta as a loving and caring wife, mother and grandmother who has left a vacuum that will be difficult to fill. He prayed Allah to grant her soul Aljanatu Firdausi and strength for the family to bear the loss.